  "version": 1,
  "updated_at": "2026-02-17",
  "title": {
    "en": "The Tomb Was Sealed"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en": [
      "The religious leaders remembered that Jesus had spoken of rising again.",
      "They asked that the tomb be made secure."
    ]
  },
  "blocks": {
    "en": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "security",
        "icon": "lock",
        "label": { "en": "Make the Tomb Secure" },
        "lines": [
          "The chief priests said to Pilate,",
          "“He said, ‘After three days I will rise again.’",
          "Give the order for the tomb to be made secure.”",
          "Pilate answered,",
          "“Take a guard.",
          "Go, make it as secure as you know how.”",
          "So they sealed the stone",
          "and posted the guard."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "third_day",
        "icon": "schedule",
        "label": { "en": "The First Day of the Week" },
        "lines": [
          "After the Sabbath, at dawn",
          "on the first day of the week,",
          "Mary Magdalene and the other Mary",
          "went to look at the tomb."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "empty_tomb",
        "icon": "auto_awesome",
        "label": { "en": "He Is Not Here" },
        "lines": [
          "An angel said to the women,",
          "“Do not be afraid.",
          "You are looking for Jesus,",
          "who was crucified.",
          "He is not here;",
          "he has risen,",
          "just as he said.",
          "Come and see the place",
          "where he lay.”"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "question": {
    "en": "Why do you think the tomb was sealed and guarded? What does the empty tomb force people to consider?"
  },
  "further_reading": {
    "en": ["Matthew 27:62–66", "Matthew 28:1–6"]
  }
}
